d 17:54.\n\nThe current heartbeat check at 17:54 shows the main cron jobs and DTLX monitor are all running, which matches the baseline state. The other cron job that reported at 17:51 has already completed. I need to verify if there's been any actual state change or if I'm just seeing timing differences in the heartbeat reports. So the session is technically still marked as running even though the runtime has ended, which is why the session history shows `status: \"running\"` but `endedAt` is set. The key thing is that nothing has actually changed since the last report—both cron jobs are still running as they were, the other ones finished normally without issues, and there are no new failures or blockers to report. Everything checks out and the system is stable. All the MCP services are functioning normally—Stitch, Confluence, and GitLab are all operational. Since there are no blockers or new failures, the pipeline status remains healthy. Comparing against the previous state, nothing has changed: all the cron jobs are still running as expected, and the Telegram group sessions remain stable. I'm confirming the pipeline is healthy with no new changes to report."},{"type":"text","text":"Comparing current session state (17:54 UTC) against baseline (17:51 UTC):\n\n**Baseline:** `cron:6f3323ef` ✅ `cron:ed2d0b5d` ✅ `cron:e7885813` ✅ — all running. `telegram:group:-5163901258` done (normal lifecycle).\n\n**Current:** All 3 cron sessions still running. `telegram:group:-5163901258` running (updatedAt advancing normally to 17:47 UTC). No new failures, no new blockers, no state transitions.\n\n**No change. Silent exit.**"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":331,"output":664,"totalTokens":46180,"cacheRead":14264,"cacheWrite":30921,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776189339771,"responseId":"062db29c3c3f34e9903574979f062e46","__openclaw":{"id":"501eed99","seq":7}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:te